Reproductive tract variable in length, extending part-way along dorsal oesophageal gland, to nerve ring or to base of stylet knobs; outstretched or with one flexure (posterior to gland or posterior to nerve ring); oviduct with two oocytes per row; uterus mostly containing no eggs (one egg in 4 of
21 specimens
); vulva mostly a depressed slit (in 14 of
21 specimens
), occasionally with protruding lips (in 5 of
21 specimens
), rarely flat (in 2 of
21 specimens
). Anus opening into a small depression in the cuticle. Tail short, conoid, with small volume; length 1– 1.8 times anal body diameter, tip rounded.
